# load data
RED <- raster("Merced20211008/LC08_CU_002009_20211008_20211022_02_TOA_B4.tif")
NIR <- raster("Merced20211008/LC08_CU_002009_20211008_20211022_02_TOA_B5.tif")

merced_road_shp <- st_read("Merced_County_Road_Centerlines/Road_Centerlines.shp")
## Reading layer `Road_Centerlines' from data source 
##   `C:\Users\freex\Documents\GitHub\30DayMapChallenge\Merced_County_Road_Centerlines\Road_Centerlines.shp' 
##   using driver `ESRI Shapefile'
## Simple feature collection with 14048 features and 65 fields
## Geometry type: LINESTRING
## Dimension:     XY
## Bounding box:  xmin: -121.2226 ymin: 36.81182 xmax: -120.0895 ymax: 37.63291
## Geodetic CRS:  WGS 84
merced_road_df <- as.data.frame(st_coordinates(merced_road_shp)) %>%
  filter(X > -120.55) %>%
  filter(X < -120.40) %>%
  filter(Y > 37.27) %>%
  filter(Y < 37.38)

NDVI

NDVI <- (NIR - RED) / (NIR + RED)
NDVI_df <- NDVI %>%
  projectRaster(crs = "+proj=longlat +datum=WGS84") %>%
  as("SpatialPixelsDataFrame") %>% 
  as.data.frame()
Merced_NDVI_df <- NDVI_df %>%
  filter(x > -120.55) %>%
  filter(x < -120.40) %>%
  filter(y > 37.27) %>%
  filter(y < 37.38)
summary(Merced_NDVI_df$layer)
##    Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max. 
## -0.1153  0.1037  0.1503  0.1521  0.1958  0.5171
Merced_NDVI_df %>%
  ggplot() +
  geom_tile(aes(x = x, y = y, fill = layer)) +
  geom_sf(data = merced_road_shp) +
  xlim(-120.55, -120.40) +
  ylim(37.27, 37.38) +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_blank(),
        axis.text.y = element_blank(),
        axis.ticks = element_blank(),
        panel.background = element_blank(),
        panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),
        plot.subtitle = element_text(color = "black", hjust = 0.5, size = 15),
        plot.title = element_text(color = "darkgreen", hjust = 0.5, size = 30)) + 
  scale_fill_gradient(low = "gray", high = "green", name = "NDVI") +
  labs(title = "NDVI",
       subtitle = "30 Day Map Challenge Day 10: Raster",
       caption = "USGS LandSat8 Data",
       x = "", y = "")
